      <hr />
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="conventions">
         <div>
            <p><strong>Display Constants</strong></p>
            <div class="table">
               <table>
                  <tr>
                     <td>-</td>
                     <td><em>[dash associated with the content of subfield $v,
                              $x, $y, and $z]</em></td>
                  </tr>
               </table>
            </div>
            <p>Dash (-) that precedes a subdivision in an extended 600 subject heading is not carried
            in the MARC record. It may be system generated as a display constant associated with the
            content of subfield $v, $x, $y, and $z.</p>
            <div class="example">
               <table>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="5%"> </td>
                     <td colspan="9">
                        <div class="captiontext">Content designated field :</div>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td><strong>600</strong></td>
                     <td colspan="9"><strong>10</strong><strong>$a</strong>Brunhoff, Jean de,<strong>$d</strong>1899-1937<strong>$x</strong>Characters<strong>$x</strong>Babar.
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td></td>
                     <td colspan="9">
                        <div class="captiontext">Display example:</div>Brunhoff, Jean de, 1899-1937-Characters-Babar.
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
               </table>
            </div>
